Unfortunately and write this respectfully... its time for the tweeps, paid advisors and others who have presided over the cannabis stock decimation to take an account of their failed analysis of fundamentals and their wrong sided view of regulation and legislative relief.

Markets rarely lie. $MSOS is -65% year to date. Many have hurt their reputations and businesses and those followers that have embraced their views. Repeating the same things on twitter - over and over again - is the definition of insanity (as Einstein wrote). Its time to

stop tweeting and postulating and to somehow learn from their poorly timed and bullish narrative. I am not calling out any person or thread specifically. Buffett once said criticize by category and praise by individual. But, instead of the steady and wrong continuum of optimistic
tweets it is time to look inward and some to be more honest with themselves. Maybe, then, cannabis stocks can bottom... @threadreaderapp unroll
